egt die Grundlagen des Konstruierens mit lebenden Bäumen dar.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 4aAstverwachsungen. 4aBaumarchitektur. 4aBaumbrücken. 4aBaumhäuser. 4aGrüne Architektur. 4aLebende Architektur. 4aTanzlinden. 7aARCHITECTURE / Methods & Materials.2bisacsh  aBaubotanik.  aPrimack.  aTrees.  aarbotecture.  abotanic architecture.  adance linden tree.  ainosculation.  aliving architecture.  aplane trees.  awillow trees.1 aDümpelmann, Sonja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchönle, Daniel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2022z9783110992793oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978303560331640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303560342240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035603422423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783035603422/original  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DADb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022